300-{
301-	// Plan 11-09.15 Iter-4 (Test A): CPU-side VB snapshot for radial-pattern
302-	// investigation. Iter-3's per-fan-draw state diagnostic showed 15/16 fan
303-	// samples at byte offset 0 + same shared-ring VB pointer; the math on
304-	// the fan-list IB path is clean (CODEX Bucket A verified) so the next
305-	// question is whether the engine is writing a real quad into CPU memory
306-	// or degenerate/collapsed data. Read from s_lastLockedSliceCPUPtr BEFORE
307-	// Unmap -- after Unmap the mapped memory may be rotated by the driver
308-	// (D3D11_USAGE_DYNAMIC + WRITE_DISCARD semantics).
309-	//
310:	// Filtered to fan-shaped slices (numberOfVertices==4 && vertexSize==24:
311-	// position(12)+color(4)+UV(8)) to keep log volume low. Sampled like the
312-	// Iter-3 diagnostic: first 5 + every 500th.
313-	{
